      "job_description": "Would you like to be part of our extraordinary and dynamic team that is Engineering the Impossible!\n\nWe are hiring an experienced .NET Web Developer with a passion for cutting-edge technologies.\n\nTo learn more about us, check out our videos: https://www.youtube.com/c/PackSmartSolutions/videos\n\nWhat we are looking for\n• Participate in the next generation architectural design, technology selection, development, validation and deployment.\n• Review requirements and collaborate cross functionally for work scope\n• Design and develop full stack of web application using modern technologies.\n• Design database and improve the performance of database.\n• Test and maintain software products to ensure strong functionality and optimization.\n• Create and maintain design documents, development journal, technical notes and reports.\n• Software deployment, on-site and remote technical support if needed\n\nWhat you will bring\n• BS/CS/EE or higher in computer science or related, or proof of exceptional skills in related fields, with practical engineering experience.\n• Proficient in C#, ASP.Net, .Net Core\n• Experience with React, Angular, Node.JS\n• Understanding of Object-Oriented design and practices\n• Worked with HTML, XML, CSS, SQL, JSON, RESTful API\n• Familiar with current UX/UI best practices\n• Occasional travel\n\nJoin The Pack-Smart Team because:\n• We care for YOU: We work to develop, engage, empower and energize our people through coaching, treat days, free gourmet beverages, team events and more. Endless opportunities for professional growth and development.\n• We offer competitive Total Rewards: Competitive starting salaries from $80k per year, paid vacation, comprehensive health and dental benefits including Life Insurance for self and dependents, RRSP program and numerous store discounts.\n• We offer a Modern Work Environment: A safe, dynamic and fast-paced environment where inclusion, learning and collaboration are key to successfully delivering exemplary solutions. You get the chance to work with innovative technology, advanced tools and software.\n• Our Team: We operate with a non-conventional philosophy of inter-disciplinary collaboration and innovative mindset. We wouldn’t succeed without the shared passion for making the world a more advanced place.\n\nWe welcome and encourage applications from people with disabilities. Accommodations are available on request during the hiring process.",
